[S7 Agent] Final Answer:
The song "Ordinary" by Alex Warren centers on the theme of finding profound, transcendent meaning within a relationship, even when the world around them feels bleak or fading. 

The lyrics suggest a sense of disillusionment with the surrounding environment—noting that "the holy water's watered down" and the town has "lost its faith." In the face of this decay and the feeling that time 
is running out, the narrator chooses to reject the mundane. Instead, they commit to making their shared life a "masterpiece."

Ultimately, the song portrays the partner as a sanctuary. The narrator describes the relationship as "out of the ordinary," suggesting that their love provides a sense of purpose and intensity that elevates 
their existence above the common, everyday experience. It is a celebration of finding something sacred and extraordinary in a person, effectively creating a private world that feels immune to the fading colors 
of the outside world.
